In a large resealable plastic bag, combine the first seven ingredients; mix well. Add chicken; seal bag and refrigerate for at least 8 hours. Drain and reserve marinade. In a large skillet over medium heat, brown the chicken in oil. Add the marinade and 1 cup water; bring to a boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 25-30 minutes or until chicken juices run clear. Combine cornstarch and remaining water; stir into pan. Bring to a boil; boil for 2 minutes, stirring constantly. Stir in parsley.